fulltitle: John Stockwell: The CIA in the Age of Glasnost
title: John Stockwell: The CIA in the Age of Glasnost
_filename: _John Stockwell - The CIA in the Age of Glasnost.webm
description: John Stockwell is the highest-ranking CIA officer to go public. During his 13-year tenure at the Agency, he was involved in operations in the Congo and Vietnam. As Director of the Angola Task Force, he ran the secret war in that country. He is the author of In Search of Enemies and The Praetorian Guard.
